    {
      "id": "palm.western_planetary_mounds.locations",
      "domain": "palm",
      "topic": "planetary_mounds",
      "originalText": "The ball of the thumb is called the mountain of Venus; the base of the index finger the mountain of Jupiter; the root of the middle finger the mountain of Saturn; the bases of ring and little finger the mountains of the Sun and Mercury. Above the mountain of Mercury, and between the lines of head and heart is the mountain of Mars, and above the line of heart the mountain of the Moon.",
      "normalizedClaim": "1911年《大英百科全书》的西方手相条目记录了金星、木星、土星、太阳、水星、火星和月丘的命名与位置；这不是中国八卦掌位体系，也不足以支持旧库细分的火星正丘、负丘和平原。",
      "sourceRefIds": ["britannica-1911-palmistry-planetary-mounts"],
      "interpretationStatus": "historical_western_witness",
      "runtimePolicy": "cultural_learning_with_citation",
      "runtimeEligible": true
